torage API:Copy codedocument.getElementById('settings-form').addEventListener('submit', function(event) {\\n  // Prevent the form from being submitted\\n  event.preventDefault();\\n\\n  // Get all the form inputs\\n  var inputs = this.elements;\\n\\n  // Loop through the inputs and store their values in local storage\\n  for (var i = 0; i < inputs.length; i++) {\\n    localStorage.setItem(inputs[i].name, inputs[i].value);\\n  }\\n});\\nThis code listens for the submit event on the form and prevents it from being submitted to the server. It then gets all the form inputs and stores their values in local storage using their name as the key and their value as the value.You can then retrieve the stored values from local storage as needed by using the localStorage.getItem() function and passing in the key for the value you want to retrieve.I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any questions.\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"message\": \"i have made `upload`  folder in `/home/hemang/Downloads/notebook_scripts/templates` to split the `uplaod.html` into all the files and I am using `index.html` to access `/upload` route, but it shows this error ```Not Found\\nThe requested URL was not found on the server. If you entered the URL manually please check your spelling and try again.```\",\n        \"response\": \"Here is an improved version of the code for the settings.html page:Copy code<!DOCTYPE html>\\n<html>\\n  <head>\\n    <title>Display Settings</title>\\n    <script>\\n      // Add a submit event listener to the form\\n      document.getElementById('settings-form').addEventListener('submit', function(event) {\\n        // Prevent the form from being submitted\\n        event.preventDefault();\\n\\n        // Get all the form inputs\\n        var inputs = this.elements;\\n\\n        // Loop through the inputs and store their values in local storage\\n        for (var i = 0; i < inputs.length; i++) {\\n          localStorage.setItem(inputs[i].name, inputs[i].value);\\n     