ead of your HTML file:Copy code<script src=\\\"https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js\\\"></script>\\nAlternatively, you can include jQuery by downloading it and adding it to your project locally. Make sure to include it before the script that uses it.Once you have included jQuery, the $ symbol will be defined and the error should disappear.It's also worth noting that the window.onload event is unnecessary in this case, as you are not using it to execute any code. You can remove the window.onload function wrapper and simply define the saveSettings function in the global scope. This should also fix the Uncaught ReferenceError: saveSettings is not defined error that you mentioned in your previous message.\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"message\": \"Here is an example of how you could modify popup.html to implement step 1:Copy code<!DOCTYPE html>\\n<html>\\n  <head>\\n    <title>ChatGPTPublish</title>\\n  </head>\\n  <body>\\n    <!-- Add a button to login with GitHub -->\\n    <button id=\\\"login-button\\\">Login with GitHub</button>\\n    <!-- Add a form to select the repository and enter the auth token -->\\n    <form id=\\\"publish-form\\\">\\n      <!-- Add radio buttons to select the repository -->\\n      <input type=\\\"radio\\\" id=\\\"repository-1\\\" name=\\\"repository\\\" value=\\\"USERNAME/REPO1\\\">\\n      <label for=\\\"repository-1\\\">Repository 1</label><br>\\n      <input type=\\\"radio\\\" id=\\\"repository-2\\\" name=\\\"repository\\\" value=\\\"USERNAME/REPO2\\\">\\n      <label for=\\\"repository-2\\\">Repository 2</label><br>\\n      <!-- Add an input field for the auth token -->\\n      <label for=\\\"auth-token\\\">Auth Token:</label><br>\\n      <input type=\\\"text\\\" id=\\\"auth-token\\\"><br>\\n      <!-- Add a button to publish the chat -->\\n      <button id=\\\"publish-button\\\">Publish</button>\\n    </form>\\n    <!-- Add a div to display the response from the server -->\\n    <div id=\\\"response\\\"></div>\\n\\n    <!-- Add t