ny issues with loading the script, such as network errors or CORS issues.If the MUI library script is being loaded correctly and you are still seeing the M is not defined error, it could be that the MUI library has not finished initializing when your code is trying to use it. In this case, you can try wrapping your code that uses the M variable in a function and calling the function after the MUI library has finished initializing, like this:Copy code$(document).ready(function() {\\n  M.AutoInit(); \\n  // Call the function that uses the M variable after MUI has finished initializing\\n  yourFunction();\\n});\\nI hope this helps! Let me know if you have any further questions or if you need more assistance.\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"message\": \"The error you are seeing is due to a security feature in your web browser that prevents a page from being embedded in a frame or iframe if the page's Content Security Policy (CSP) specifies that it should not be allowed. In this case, the page you are trying to embed (https://github.com/) has specified in its CSP that it should not be embedded in a frame, and that is why you are seeing the error.To resolve this issue, you will need to modify your code to open the GitHub login page in a new tab or window, rather than trying to embed it in a frame or iframe. Here is an example of how you can modify the code in popup.html to open the GitHub login page in a new tab when the \\\"Login with GitHub\\\" button is clicked:Copy code<!-- Add the \\\"Login with GitHub\\\" button -->\\n<button id=\\\"login-button\\\">Login with GitHub</button>\\n\\n<!-- Add the JavaScript code to open the GitHub login page in a new tab when the button is clicked -->\\n<script>\\n  // Add a click event listener to the \\\"Login with GitHub\\\" button\\n  document.getElementById(\\\"login-button\\\").addEventListener(\\\"click\\\", function() {\\n    // Open the GitHub login page in a new tab\\n    window.open(\\\"https://github.com/login\\\", \\\"_blank\\\");\\n  });\\n</script>\\nThis code will open the GitHub login page in a new tab when the \\\"Login with GitHub\\\" button is clicked, rather than trying to embed it in a frame or iframe. Once you have logged in to GitHub and authenticated the extension, you will need to store the authentication token in your extension's background script or content script, so that it can be used to make API requests to GitHub on behalf of the authenticated user. You can use the chrome.storage API to store the token in your extension, or you can use a different method such as sending the token to your server and storing it there.\",\n        \"response\": \"It looks like the error is caused by trying to use the M object before it is defined.To fix the error, you can move the code that initializes the M object to the beginning of the script, before you try to use it.Here's the modified code:Copy code<html>\\n  <head>\\n    <title>Display Settings</title>\\n    <link href=\\\"//cdn.muicss.com/mui-0.10.3/css/mui.min.css\\\" rel=\\\"stylesheet\\\" type=\\\"text/css\\\" />\\n    <script src=\\\"//cdn.muicss.com/mui-0.10.3/js/mui.min.js\\\"></script>\\n    <script src=\\\"https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js\\\"></script>\\n\\n </head>\\n  \\n  <body>\\n  {% include 'navigation.html' %}\\n  <div class=\\\"container\\\">\\n    <h1 class=\\\"mui--text-center mui--text-display1\\\">Display Settings</h1>\\n    <div class=\\\"mui-container\\\">\\n      <div class=\\\"mui-panel\\\">\\n        {% for parameterName, parameter in parameters.items() %}\\n        <div class=\\\"mui-form-group\\\" style=\\\"padding: 10px\\\">\\n          <label for=\\\"{{ parameterName }}\\\">{{ parameterName }}</label>\\n          <select id=\\\"{{ parameterName }}\\\" name=\\\"{{ parameterName }}\\\" class=\\\"mui-form-control\\\">\\n            {% for value in parameter.possible_values %}\\n              <option value=\\\"{{ value }}\\\" {% if value == parameter.value %}selected{% endif %}>{{ value }}</option>\\n            {% endfor %}\\n          </select>\\n        </div>\\n        {% endfor %}\\n      </div>\\n      <div class=\\\"mui-container mui--text-center\\\">\\n        <button class=\\\"mui-btn mui-btn--primary mui-btn--raised\\\" type=\\\"button\\\" id=\\\"save-button\\\" onclick=\\\"saveSettings();\\\">Save</button>\\n      </div>\\n    </div>\\n    <div id=\\\"success-message\\\" class=\\\"row\\\" style=\\\"display: none;\\\">\\n      <div class=\\\"col s12\\\">\\n        <div class=\\\"card-panel green lighten-4\\\">\\n          Settings saved successfully!\\n        </div>\\n      </div>\\n    </div>\\n  </div>\\n  <!-- Add a script to handle saving and loading the settings -->\\n  <script>\\n    $(document).ready(function() {\\n      M.AutoInit(); \\n    });\\n\\n    window.onload = function() {\\n      // Send an AJAX request to the backend to get the settings from the database\\n      var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();\\n      xhr.open('GET', '/get_settings');\\n      xhr.onload = function() {\\n        if (xhr.status === 200) {\\n          // If the request was successful, set the form input values to the returned settings\\n          var settings = JSON.parse(xhr.responseText);\\n          for (var parameter in settings) {\\n            document.getElementsByName(parameter)[0].value = settings[parameter];\\n          }\\n       \\n\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"message\": \"my `popup.html` code looks like this. ```<!DOCTYPE html>\\n<html>\\n  <head>\\n    <script src=\\\"popup.js\\\" nonce=\\\"randomstring\\\" content_security_policy=\\\"script-src 'unsafe-inline';\\\"></script>\\n    <title>ChatGPTPublish</title>\\n  </head>\\n  <body>\\n    <!-- Add an iframe element to display the GitHub login page -->\\n    <iframe id=\\\"login-iframe\\\" src=\\\"https://github.com/login\\\"></iframe>\\n\\n    <!-- Add the \\\"Login with GitHub\\\" button -->\\n    <button id=\\\"login-button\\\">Login with GitHub</button>\\n\\n    <!-- Add the JavaScript code to open the GitHub login page in a new tab when the button is clicked -->\\n    <script nonce=\\\"randomstring\\\" content_security_policy=\\\"script-src 'unsafe-inline';\\\">\\n      // Add a click event listener to the \\\"Login with GitHub\\\" button\\n      document.getElementById(\\\"login-button\\\").addEventListener(\\\"click\\\", function() {\\n        // Open the GitHub login page in a new tab\\n        window.open(\\\"https://github.com/login\\\", \\\"_blank\\\");\\n      });\\n    </script>\\n    <div id=\\\"repository-list\\\"></div>\\n    <button id=\\\"publish-button\\\">Publish</button>\\n  </body>\\n</html>\\n\\n``` still I am getting this error ```\\n\\ufeff\\npopup.html:15 Refused to execute inline script because it violates the following Content Security Policy directive: \\\"script-src 'self' blob: filesystem:\\\". Either the 'unsafe-inline' keyword, a hash ('sha256-/93BJ455Kqzxr8bV++zM+v+8utL6doZscu+non1OLF4='), or a nonce ('nonce-...') is required to enable inline execution.``` give me code to resolve this error\",\n        \"response\": \"It looks like this code is trying to send an HTTP GET request to the server to retrieve the current settings and then update the form input values with the returned data.The window.onload event is fired when the page finishes loading, so this code will run when the page is finished loading. The XMLHttpRequest object is used to send an HTTP request to the server. The open method initializes the request, the onload event is fired when the request is successful, and the send method sends the request.If the request is successful (i.e. the status code is 200), the response text is parsed into a JavaScript object and the form input values are updated with the values from the object. If the request fails (i.e. the status code is not 200), an error message is displayed.Is there anything else you'd like to know about this code?\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"message\": \"To resolve this error, you need to either include the 'unsafe-inline' keyword in the script-src directive of your Content Security Policy (CSP), or you need to use a nonce or a hash to whitelist the inline script.Here is an example of how you could modify your popup.html file to include a nonce:Copy code<!DOCTYPE html>\\n<html>\\n  <head>\\n    <script src=\\\"popup.js\\\" nonce=\\\"randomstring\\\" content_security_policy=\\\"script-src 'unsafe-inline';\\\"></script>\\n    <title>ChatGPTPublish</title>\\n  </head>\\n  <body>\\n    <!-- Add an iframe element to display the GitHub login page -->\\n    <iframe id=\\\"login-iframe\\\" src=\\\"https://github.com/login\\\"></iframe>\\n\\n    <!-- Add the \\\"Login with GitHub\\\" button -->\\n    <button id=\\\"login-button\\\">Login with GitHub</button>\\n\\n    <!-- Add the JavaScript code to open the GitHub login page in a new tab when the button is clicked -->\\n    <script nonce=\\\"randomstring\\\" content_security_policy=\\\"script-src 'unsafe-inline';\\\">\\n      // Add a click event listener to the \\\"Login with GitHub\\\" button\\n      document.getElementById(\\\"login-button\\\").addEventListener(\\\"click\\\", function() {\\n        // Open the GitHub login page in a new tab\\n        window.open(\\\"https://github.com/login\\\", \\\"_blank\\\");\\n      });\\n    </script>\\n    <div id=\\\"repository-list\\\"></div>\\n    <button id=\\\"publish-button\\\">Publish</button>\\n  </body>\\n</html>\\nNote that the nonce attribute is included in the script element and the value of the nonce attribute is the same as the value specified in the script element for the popup.js script. This will allow the inline script to be executed.Alternatively, you could use a hash or a nonce in the script-src directive of the CSP to whitelist the inline script.For example, you could use a hash like this:Copy code<!DOCTYPE html>\\n<html>\\n  <head>\\n    <script src=\\\"popup.js\\\" nonce=\\\"randomstring\\\" content_security_policy=\\\"script-src 'sha256-/93BJ455Kqzxr8bV++zM+v+8