ase')\\n\\n# Create a cursor object to execute SQL statements\\ncursor = cnx.cursor()\\n\\n# Create the advertisement table\\ntable_sql = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\nCREATE TABLE advertisement (\\n  id INT(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,\\n  file_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,\\n  file_path VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,\\n  start_time DATETIME NOT NULL,\\n  end_time DATETIME NOT NULL,\\n  PRIMARY KEY (id)\\n);\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\ncursor.execute(table_sql)\\n\\n# Commit the changes to the database\\ncnx.commit()\\n\\n# Close the cursor and connection\\ncursor.close()\\ncnx.close()\\nThis code creates a MySQL database named your_database, and a table called advertisement within it. The advertisement table has columns for storing the file name, file path, start time, and end time of the advertisement.Once you have created the database and table, you can use Python and SQL statements to insert the advertisement data into the table when the user submits the advertisement upload form.Here is an example of how you can insert the advertisement data into the advertisement table using Python:Copy codeimport mysql.connector\\n\\n# Connect to the MySQL server\\ncnx = mysql.connector.connect(user='your_username', password='your_password', host='localhost', database='your_database')\\n\\n# Create a cursor object to execute SQL statements\\ncursor = cnx.cursor()\\n\\n# Insert the advertisement data into the table\\ninsert_sql = \\\"INSERT INTO advertisement (file_name, file_path, start_time, end_time) VALUES (%s, %s, %s, %s)\\\"\\ncursor.execute(insert_sql, (file_name, file_path, start_time, end_time))\\n\\n# Commit the changes to the database\\ncnx.commit()\\n\\n# Close the cursor and connection\\ncursor.close()\\ncnx.close()\\nThis code inserts a row into the advertisement table with the values for the file name, file path, start time, and end time that are passed to the execute function.To integrate the database with the upload.html template file, you will need to modify the Flask route that handles the su