\"DELETE /delete-ad/3 HTTP/1.1\\\" 404 -`\\nWhat code snippet should I add to `flaskBackend.py` ?\",\n        \"response\": \"Here is a sample script that you can use to run the command in the background if the current time is within the start and end times of an ad in the ads table in the displayad database:Copy codeimport mysql.connector\\nimport os\\nimport subprocess\\nimport time\\n\\n# Connect to the database\\ncnx = mysql.connector.connect(user='root', password='mysql123!@#', host='localhost', database='displayad')\\ncursor = cnx.cursor()\\n\\n# Set the path to the image folder\\nimage_folder = '/home/hemang/Downloads/notebook_scripts/displyaAdData'\\n\\nwhile True:\\n    # Get the current time\\n    current_time = time.strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\\\")\\n\\n    # Execute the query to get the ads that are currently active\\n    query = f'SELECT * FROM ads WHERE start_time <= \\\"{current_time}\\\" AND end_time >= \\\"{current_time}\\\"'\\n    cursor.execute(query)\\n\\n    # Fetch the rows\\n    ads = cursor.fetchall()\\n\\n    # Loop through the active ads\\n    for ad in ads:\\n        # Get the image file name\\n        image_name = ad[5]\\n\\n        # Check if the image file exists\\n        image_path = os.path.join(image_folder, image_name)\\n        if os.path.exists(image_path):\\n            # Run the command in the background\\n            command = f'sudo ./demo -D 1 {image_name} --led-no-hardware --led-rows=32 --led-cols=64 --led-parallel=3 --led-slowdown-gpio=4'\\n            subprocess.Popen(command, shell=True)\\n        else:\\n            print(f'Image file {image_name} not found')\\n\\n    # Sleep for 1 minute before checking the ads again\\n    time.sleep(60)\\n\\n# Close the connection to the database\\ncursor.close()\\ncnx.close()\\nThis script will continuously loop and check the ads table every minute to see if there are any ads that are currently active. If there are, it will run the command to display the ad on the LED matrix. If the image file specified in the file_name column of the ads table does not exist, it will print an error message.Note: You will need to modify the image_folder variable to the correct path of the folder where the image files are stored. You will also need to modify the command variable to include the correct path to the demo executable file.\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"message\": \"To delete an ad, you need to handle the DELETE request in your Flask server. You can do this by defining a new route in flaskBackend.py that takes in the ad id as a parameter and deletes the corresponding ad from the database.Here is an example of how you can do this:Copy code@app.route('/delete-ad/<int:id>', methods=['DELETE'])\\ndef delete_ad(id):\\n    # Connect to the database\\n    conn = sqlite3.connect('ads.db')\\n    c = conn.cursor()\\n\\n    # Delete the ad with the specified id\\n    c.execute(\\\"DELETE FROM ads WHERE id=?\\\", (id,))\\n    conn.commit()\\n    conn.close()\\n\\n    return '', 204\\nThis route will handle DELETE requests to /delete-ad/<id>, where <id> is the id of the ad to be deleted. It will delete the ad with the specified id from the ads table in the database, and return a 204 No Content response.You can then make a DELETE request from your client-side code (in schedule.html) to this route using the fetch function when the user clicks the delete button.Here is an example of how you can do this in the deleteAd function in schedule.html:Copy codefunction deleteAd(id) {\\n  fetch(`/delete-ad/${id}`, {method: 'DELETE'})\\n    .then(response => {\\n      if (response.ok) {\\n        // Refresh the table to show the updated data\\n        fetchData();\\n      }\\n    });\\n}\\nThis will send a DELETE request to the /delete-ad/<id> route with the specified ad id, and refresh the table to show the updated data if the DELETE request was successful.I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any questions.\",\n        \"response\": \"To reset the root user password for